<p>In celebration of the United Nations' first annual International Day of Sport for Development and Peace, the Lao Rugby Federation is bringing together some local and international teams for a friendly competition. </p><p>The Hong Kong Vandals will be touring Laos, and visiting the LRF's own sport for development project in Nonghet, Xieng Khouang.  They will hold a friendly inter-village youth rugby tournament between the 12 villages where Lao Rugby works.</p><p>The teams will play together to celebrate the potential for sport to positively bring together people of different ages, cultures, and backgrounds.</p><p>Lear more <a href="http://www.april6.org/en/play-your-peace/upcoming-events/sport-for-peace-and-friendship-games.html">here</a></p>